Vice President Kamala Harris welcomed Chairman Raul Ruiz and members of the Congressional Hispanic Caucus to the Vice President's Ceremonial Office. They discussed various issues challenging the country, including the COVID-19 vaccination efforts and support for other nations. They also addressed the impact of the pandemic on small businesses, particularly Latino and Hispanic-owned businesses, and the need for support through the American Rescue Plan, American Jobs Plan, and American Families Plan. The Vice President emphasized the importance of addressing the root causes of migration from the Northern Triangle countries and discussed efforts to bring federal agencies, American foundations, and private corporations together to support the region. She highlighted the impacts of poverty, food insecurity, corruption, violence, and gender inequality and stressed the need for a long-term approach to addressing these issues.